    <description>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>General A429 Description</title>
        <para>
          This data module provides a general description of the ARINC 429 bus implementation
          in the BWB-Q100 Integrated Modular Avionics (IMA) system.
        </para>
        
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Purpose</title>
          <para>
            The ARINC 429 data bus provides reliable, unidirectional communication between
            avionics systems. It is used for transmitting flight-critical data including:
          </para>
          <para>
            <randomList>
              <listItem><para>Air data parameters (airspeed, altitude, vertical speed)</para></listItem>
              <listItem><para>Navigation information (heading, position, track)</para></listItem>
              <listItem><para>Engine data (N1, N2, temperatures)</para></listItem>
              <listItem><para>Flight control surface positions</para></listItem>
              <listItem><para>System status information</para></listItem>
            </randomList>
          </para>
        </levelledPara>
        
        <levelledPara>
          <title>System Overview</title>
          <para>
            The BWB-Q100 implements 16 ARINC 429 channels (8 receive, 8 transmit) operating
            at both low speed (12.5 kbps) and high speed (100 kbps).
          </para>
          <para>
            For detailed architecture information, refer to data module 
            DMC-Q100-A-42-61-00-00A-010A-D-EN-US (A429 Bus Architecture).
          </para>
        </levelledPara>
        
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Standards Compliance</title>
          <para>
            This implementation complies with:
          </para>
          <para>
            <randomList>
              <listItem><para>ARINC Specification 429, Mark 33</para></listItem>
              <listItem><para>DO-178C Level A (Software)</para></listItem>
              <listItem><para>DO-254 Level A (Hardware)</para></listItem>
              <listItem><para>DO-160G (Environmental)</para></listItem>
            </randomList>
          </para>
        </levelledPara>
        
      </levelledPara>
    </description>
